#Text=4. Numerical Simulation
#Text=4.1. The Parameters Selection of Simulation Model
#Text=The MATLAB is adopted for system modeling and simulation , and ode45 algorithm is employed .
#Text=Considering that the pressure pulsation caused by the oil pump is 12 % , the speed of plunger pump is 990 rpm , the number of plungers is seven , so the pulsation frequency is 116 Hz .
#Text=The nominal parameters of the hydraulic screw down system of the rolling mill used in the simulation are shown in Table 1 .
#Text=4.2. Simulation Results and Analysis
#Text=4.2.1. Influence of Different Equivalent Damping Coefficients on Nonlinear Dynamic Behavior
#Text=It is found that different equivalent damping coefficients have a great influence on the nonlinear system .

#Text=Figure 4
#Text=shows the vibration simulations that result from the hydraulic cylinder of the rolling mill with different equivalent damping coefficients under the same conditions .
#Text=Through the vibration displacement curve , it can be clearly found that the vibration amplitude of vibration displacement significantly increases with the damping coefficient decreasing .
#Text=Through the phase diagram , it can be found that the system moves from a stable state to a periodic vibration state and becomes unstable with the damping coefficient decreasing .
#Text=From the perspective of vibration intensity , as shown in
#Text=Figure 5
#Text=, it can clearly be found that the vibration intensity of the system can be effectively suppressed by increasing the damping .
#Text=4.2.2. Influence of Different Leakage Coefficients on Nonlinear Dynamic Behavior
#Text=The hydraulic system is sealed with a rubber ring .
#Text=Due to the influence of oil temperature and oil cleanliness , the seal of the hydraulic cylinder will deteriorate with time , resulting in different levels of oil leakage .
#Text=By studying the influence of different internal leakage coefficients on the system , the vibration mechanism of the hydraulic cylinder caused by the leakage can be analyzed .
#Text=The leak coefficients of the hydraulic cylinder are defined as , , and .
#Text=If you take the initial value , the time – domain diagram of the vibration displacement of the cylinder and the phase diagram of the vibration displacement – speed are shown in
#Text=Figure 6
#Text=.
#Text=The vibration intensities of the system under different leakage coefficients are displayed in
#Text=Figure 7
#Text=.
#Text=Figure 6
#Text=shows the simulation results of the different leakage coefficients of the hydraulic cylinder under the same other conditions .
#Text=It can be seen from
#Text=Figure 6
#Text=that the vibration displacement of the hydraulic cylinder is small when the leakage coefficient is small .
#Text=And from the phase diagram , it can be observed that the system is convergence .
#Text=By increasing the leakage coefficient of the hydraulic cylinder , the amplitude of the vibration displacement increases .
#Text=From the phase diagram , it is difficult to stabilize from the convergence to the stage of multi-period vibration .
#Text=From the variation of vibration intensity in
#Text=Figure 7
#Text=, it can be found that the vibration intensity increases with the increase of the leakage coefficient .
#Text=Therefore , the increase of system leakage will increase the intensity of vertical vibration .
#Text=The Influences of Proportional Parameter of Vibration Controller on Nonlinear Dynamic Behavior
#Text=The proportional parameters of the controller affect the control effect of vibration suppression .
#Text=As certain process parameters or structural parameters of the system are changed , fixed parameters are bound to have adverse effects .

#Text=The PID control algorithm , with the characteristics of simple structure and convenient implementation , can be well applied to practical engineering .
#Text=In the PID control algorithm , the proportion coefficient determines the speed of system response , and the appropriate integral coefficient can effectively eliminate the system error .
#Text=Therefore , increasing the proportional coefficient can improve the response speed of the system , but a big proportional coefficient may cause the system instability .
